title: Purple Hopes
author: charlotte
text: purple hope shoots across the night sky.  i look in the mirror and wonder who i really am inside.  is it a monster that i see? or my eyes playing tricks on me? of all the lonely diamonds in the rough,  one is the hardest one to find.  that is the white blinking lights telling us what we feel inside.  little sparkles hide underneath the cracked surface,  and donâ’t shimmer again if theyâ’re stared at too long.  all those special rubies,  emeralds,  pearls arenâ’t cherished as much,  and in its life time every one of them must fade away.  none the same,  but none of them different.  for they all have those white blinking lights,  and underneath the cracked surfaces lies the truth behind their own eyes.

title: Stars to Stars, Worlds to Worlds
author: chelsea
text: in the middle of one night,    i looked at the stars,  so very bright,    and thought ''are there other worlds out  there?'',  i looked and looked,  stared and   stared,  until i fell asleep,     and dreamed of other places with    great food to eat,  then i drifted off to another dream,  to a place where fish ate ice cream,   and instead of people walking dogs,  the dogs walked the people,  and birds chased cats,  and cats chased dogs!  then i woke up and realized that there are lots of crazy and different worlds out there,  and that they were great places to be,   but where i am now is the greatest place to be,  just for me!

title: Moving
author: cheri
text: the world is changing so fast to you and me.  you're losing your friends and you're losing your ways.  you have to change schools  all over the place.  you're lonely,  sad,   and crying all at the same time.  emotions running and running through your mind.  you have to pack and unpack all over again.  driving and driving across thousands of open miles.  you have to say good-bye and you can't look back because if you do,  the tears will start.  you have to start  all over,  be a new kid in a new class.  and you don't know what's happening around you,  and why it is changing so fast but it is and that's a fact and all you know is you can't look back.

title: I'll Miss You
author: cheri
text: weâ’ve become such good friends since last november iâ’ve learned more boutâ’ you and youâ’ve gotten closer to me  and now,  you tell me your  moving.  not to another state,  atleast but,  to another city.   i will cry- but will you?? you have become such a good friend and i will miss you  it wonâ’t be the same without you here.  talking about the same boy we both liked and about our friends who sometimes didnâ’t like us.   sitting beside me,  taking notes,  borrowing pens,  competing for who has  the best creation of a name  laughing at the fact our young teacher was bald quoting movies,  line by line and word for word- sounds used when necessary   church wonâ’t be the same for the first few weeks,   neither will wednesday night activities,  but we will move on and put aside our past  still thinking about memories weâ’ve made.  weâ’ve sure had a blast.   but iâ’m sure i will see you (at least i hope) your family lives here,  so i hope you visit them often.   to my friend,  who over few months turned to my best ,  this poem is from your friend,  with love and respect.   ps.  iâ’ll miss you!!

text: (note:this poem is not about television.  i hope it gets published. thankyou, it comes straight from my heart).    pure hatred breed inside of me it was just a little portion of my heart but since the past few weeks it grew i can no longer control it.    you come back with angriness i try my best to please you all to no avail in the end i end up suffering i have built of walls you can never break.    i didnâ’t ask you to go i didnâ’t want you to go i didnâ’t want you to think of me as selfish i kept my feelings hidden.    you say i have struggles but i donâ’t it grew with me you donâ’t realize that.    i want to change but i think it is too late i wanna ask for help but i donâ’t wanna let down my wall.    i have done things that shouldnâ’t be heard of but you did  and you did nothing but look at at my face with a blank expression i was hurt.    you donâ’t know what grew with me you donâ’t seem to care i want you to i donâ’t want to break down my wall.    i love you i really do  i donâ’t trust you i wish i could.          i admit i am scared of you should i be? i give you reasonable respect do you appreciate it?   i think you are strict you say you are not your actions say you are itâ’ true.    today we are friends we seem cool for now people and time change.    as i said i wasnâ’t like this  or wasnâ’t born like this i was born with qualities they are locked within me.    you call me lazy but iâ’m not i used to do things used to but now i choose not to.    i wanted to do things when i asked  you replied with no i was always disappointed.    i chose to be this way you obviously wanted me to be this way now you complain i think you are inconsistent.    i had a best friend then i realized i was addicted to it one of man inventions the television.          now iâ’m grown up without supervision  life is sweet life is sour i live my own way.

text: i had a dog her name was snowflake,  not a hog or a milkshake.   she looked like a dark winter night,  with only one snowflake floating in the air, consistantly floating there.  she was a alaskan husky.   she was stolen, never to come back.  she was and still is my favorite dog.  i had her for about three years.  she loved me as much as i loved her.   i have had four dogs since then.  their names were p. j. ,  dexter,  shelby,  and mustang,  all of whom i loved.     all died or ran away,  on those sad days.   now i have one more dog, massey's her name,  bird hunting's her game.  she is hyper, just like me.  but still,  i remember that alaskan husky.

title: One day
author: dalton
text:
one day i woke up i don't know what time, i heard my mom in the kitchen i said that kinda rhymed, so i went
\ndownstairs and i stabbed my toe and i got mad and i said: ''ha! ha!'' because i just woke up; it all was just a dream.

title: Eat Hay
author: dalton
text: i hate you mom i say,  you big fat donkey,  go eat some hay.  when i woke the next day,  there she was eating hay,                    mom what are you doing?                  eating some like the other day.  do you do everything i say?

author: dalton
text: annoying as a bee's wippering little wings,  as scary as a mountain lion,  as brave as a cat.  for i am these things yet some of us are a few of these things.

title: Louder
author: damaris
text: louder than a monster truck,  louder than a my brother,  louder than my friends singing,  louder than a rock concert,  louder than a lion,  louder than a tuba,  that is how loud i am!!!

title: Love
author: damaris
text: you will never know true love until u have truly loved me and you will never feel  what pain really is  until u have lost me. . .

text: i don't know who i'am.  do you? i'am purple. i have white eyes.  my stomach is sort of yellow with blue dots.  no one so far can tell what i'am. can u.

title: My Dream
author: damla
text: in my world,   there are flying house,  look at the sky,  the bird sound like a song,  the sun shining,  there is lovely rabbit in the grass,  it smiling to us,  the could like sweat,  to eat.

title: Green
author: damon
text: the beautiful blades of grass,  the twinkling shine of eyes,  here and there,  there's green everywhere,  green.

title: The Tree of light
author: damon
text: the light stretched its twigs and branches,  it grew itself,  allowing me to tell the difference between night and day a tree of beauty and delight  i reached out,  though not to touch a thing,  only to rip it up with my shadow flowers pollinated by happiness the flowers that shone every colour in the world  a tree of such delicacy i crawled all over the floor 'climbing' the tree wood that could never be burnt,  cut or built with  the tree blazed onto the carpet,  and the laughter fell from my mouth burying it in breaths
